{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_zvopVY20X7JTMY9FkUaY4KzG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"tool_gfN3n8R45i3rfC0ZOUZBRyKq","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md","content":"# Research Summary — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\nStatus: reviewed\nLast reviewed: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n- FS-RBAC-03 spec requires live RBAC enforcement on critical API endpoints (POST/PUT/DELETE)\n- Need to add audit logging for role operations and 403 responses\n- Frontend role guards must sync with session updates without page refresh via WebSocket push\n- Current auth uses custom header-based profile authentication (X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Auth)\n- Frontend uses Zustand for state management (not Redux)\n- SSE (Server-Sent Events) already used for flow sessions and MCP chat\n- No existing Spring Security, JWT, or RBAC infrastructure found\n- Ticket: TST-001\n\n## AIDD:PRD_OVERRIDES\n- PRD assumes JWT-claims based RBAC (Q2=B), but codebase uses custom profile header auth\n- PRD mentions Redux (Q3=A), but actual frontend uses Zustand\n- WebSocket push mentioned in PRD, but SSE is already implemented and could be reused\n\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n- Role operations (GRANT/REVOKE) must be auditable with timestamp, user, action\n- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of session change\n- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n- Q1: Should RBAC be implemented as Spring Security filters or custom middleware? (Spring Security not currently in classpath)\n- Q2: How to handle profile-to-role mapping given current header-based auth (no JWT)?\n- Q3: Should WebSocket be introduced or extend existing SSE infrastructure for role sync?\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| No Spring Security in current classpath | High | Add spring-boot-starter-security dependency |\n| No JWT infrastructure exists | Medium | Implement custom RBAC based on profile roles from header |\n| Profile auth uses custom headers not JWT claims | Medium | Adapt RBAC to use X-Profile-Key header for identity |\n| SSE exists but PRD requires WebSocket | Low | Evaluate SSE for role push or implement WebSocket |\n| Database schema has no audit_log table | Medium | Create new migration for audit_log table |\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n- **Auth Model**: Current system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT\n- **State Management**: Frontend uses Zustand (not Redux) with persistence\n- **Real-time**: SSE already implemented for flows/MCP; WebSocket needs new infrastructure\n- **Role Storage**: Roles stored in profile document (see profileTypes.ts: `roles: z.array(z.string())`)\n\n## AIDD:INTEGRATION_POINTS\n\n### Backend Integration Points\n\n1. **Profile Header Extraction** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`)\n   - `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` creates headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth\n   - Backend must read these headers for identity\n\n2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   - All API calls use `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` for authentication\n   - Admin role APIs: `fetchAdminProfiles()`, `assignProfileRole()`, `revokeProfileRole()`\n\n3. **No Existing Security Configuration**\n   - No SecurityConfig, JWT, or @PreAuthorize annotations found\n   - No spring-boot-starter-security in build.gradle\n\n### Frontend Integration Points\n\n1. **Profile Store** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n   - Uses Zustand with persistence\n   - Profile document includes `roles: string[]`\n   - Admin check: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n\n2. **Admin Role Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`)\n   ```typescript\n   const hasAdminRole = useProfileStore(\n     (state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'),\n   );\n   ```\n\n3. **Route Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45`)\n   ```typescript\n   {hasAdminRole && (\n     <NavLink to=\"/admin/roles\" className=\"nav-link\">\n       Admin\n     </NavLink>\n   )}\n   ```\n\n4. **SSE Infrastructure** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   - `subscribeToFlowEvents()` uses EventSource for real-time updates\n   - Could be extended for role change notifications\n\n## AIDD:REUSE_CANDIDATES\n\n1. **Profile Header Parsing**\n   - Location: `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` in `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n   - Reuse: Backend should implement similar header parsing for identity extraction\n\n2. **Role Check Pattern**\n   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n   - Pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n   - Reuse: Standardize role check utility\n\n3. **Audit Event Types**\n   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/components/ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95`\n   - Events: 'profile_created', 'profile_updated', 'identity_attached', 'identity_detached', 'role_assigned', 'role_revoked'\n   - Reuse: Extend for RBAC audit events\n\n4. **SSE Event Handling**\n   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/FlowSessions.tsx`\n   - Pattern: EventSource with fallback to polling\n   - Reuse: Adapt for role change push notifications\n\n## AIDD:COMMANDS_RUN\n```bash\n# Search for auth/security patterns\ngrep -r -i \"websocket\\|socket.io\\|sse\\|event-source\\|EventSource\" frontend/src/\ngrep -r -i \"jwt\\|spring-security\\|SecurityFilter\\|@PreAuthorize\\|@Secured\" backend-mcp/src/\ngrep -r -i \"role\\|permission\\|admin\\|RBAC\" backend-mcp/src/main/java/\n\n# File discovery\nglob **/*Security*.java\nglob **/*Auth*.java\nglob **/*Config*.java\n```\n\n## AIDD:RLM_EVIDENCE\n- Status: ready (worklist pack exists but empty - no matching patterns found)\n- Pack: aidd/reports/research/TST-001-rlm.worklist.pack.json\n- Pack status: ready (0 entries - baseline established)\n- Baseline marker: links_empty_reason=no_matches\n- Findings: No existing RBAC, JWT, or Security infrastructure found\n\n## AIDD:TEST_HOOKS\n- Frontend tests: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.test.ts`\n- No backend security tests found\n- Suggested: Add RBAC middleware tests, audit logging tests\n\n## Context Pack (TL;DR)\n- **Entry points**: Backend MCP server on port 8080 (configurable via profiles)\n- **Reuse candidates**: Profile header auth, Zustand role checks, SSE infrastructure\n- **Integration points**: X-Profile-Key header parsing, role assignment/revocation APIs\n- **RLM**: No existing security patterns found (greenfield RBAC implementation)\n- **Test pointers**: profileStore.test.ts for frontend state testing\n- **Top risks**: No Spring Security, no JWT, custom auth model\n\n## Definition of reviewed\n- [x] Найдены ≥ 1 точки интеграции или явно указан baseline\n- [x] Указаны тесты/контракты или явно зафиксирован риск «нет тестов»\n- [x] Зафиксированы команды/пути сканирования и ссылки на отчёты\n\n## Контекст\n- **Цель фичи**: Implement live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend sync\n- **Scope изменений**: Backend middleware, audit database schema, frontend real-time sync\n- **Ключевые модули/директории**:\n  - Backend: `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/` - no security module exists\n  - Frontend: `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`, `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n- **Исходные артефакты**: PRD TST-001, Context Pack TST-001\n- **Логи команд / отчёты**: RLM worklist shows no existing security patterns\n\n## Точки интеграции\n\n### Backend\n1. **New RBAC Middleware** (to be created)\n   - Location: `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/security/`\n   - Integration: Spring WebFlux filter chain (WebFlux already in classpath)\n   - Headers to read: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Auth\n\n2. **Audit Log Table** (new migration needed)\n   - Location: `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n   - Schema: timestamp, user_id (profile_key), action, target_resource, result\n\n3. **Profile Service Integration**\n   - Current: Profile roles returned via API (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts:31`)\n   - Integration: Backend needs to validate roles against profile service or cache\n\n### Frontend\n1. **Profile Store Extension** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n   - Add: WebSocket/SSE listener for role changes\n   - Current: `applyProfileSnapshot()` updates profile including roles (line 57-64)\n\n2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   - Already has: `subscribeToFlowEvents()` for SSE\n   - Add: Role change subscription endpoint\n\n## Повторное использование\n\n### 1. Header-based Authentication\n- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n- **Usage**: Backend filter should parse X-Profile-Key header format: `{namespace}:{reference}`\n- **Risk**: Custom auth not standardized; document contract clearly\n- **Tests**: No existing tests for header parsing\n\n### 2. Zustand Role State Pattern\n- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n- **Usage**: `useProfileStore((state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'))`\n- **Risk**: Role check scattered across components; create reusable hook\n- **Tests**: Component-level tests needed\n\n### 3. SSE Infrastructure\n- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (subscribeToFlowEvents)\n- **Usage**: Extend for role change notifications or implement WebSocket\n- **Risk**: SSE is unidirectional; role changes may need bidirectional comms\n- **Tests**: FlowSessions.tsx has SSE usage patterns\n\n## Принятые практики\n- Profile headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth (see profileStore.ts)\n- Role storage: Array of strings in profile document (profileTypes.ts:31)\n- Audit events: Structured with eventType, metadata, timestamp (ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95)\n\n## RLM evidence\n- **No existing security modules found** - greenfield implementation required\n- **Database entities exist**: NoteEntity with user_namespace/user_reference pattern\n- **Header-based auth established**: X-Profile-Key pattern used across frontend\n\n## Паттерны/анти-паттерны\n- **Паттерны**:\n  - Header-based service-to-service auth (FlowOpsClientConfiguration.java:27-29)\n  - Zod schema validation for API responses (apiClient.ts:187-194)\n  - Audit event typing with metadata (profileTypes.ts:38-47)\n- **Анти-паттерны**:\n  - No centralized auth/authorization layer\n  - Role checks inline in components (AdminRoles.tsx, App.tsx)\n  - No standardized 403 handling\n\n## Отсутствие паттернов / отсутствующие данные\n- **No Spring Security**: spring-boot-starter-security not in build.gradle\n- **No JWT libraries**: No jjwt or similar dependencies\n- **No @PreAuthorize annotations**: No method-level security\n- **No WebSocket**: No spring-boot-starter-websocket\n- **No audit_log table**: Only note_entry and repo_rag_* tables exist\n\n## Gap-анализ\n\n| Gap | Ограничение | Компенсационный шаг |\n|-----|-------------|---------------------|\n| No Spring Security | Must add dependency | Add spring-boot-starter-security to build.gradle |\n| Custom header auth vs JWT | PRD assumes JWT claims | Adapt RBAC to extract roles from profile service using X-Profile-Key |\n| No WebSocket | PRD requires WebSocket push | Evaluate SSE extension first (lower complexity) |\n| No audit table | Need audit_log schema | Create Liquibase migration for audit_log table |\n| Zustand vs Redux | PRD mentions Redux | Update PRD to reflect actual Zustand usage |\n\n## Следующие шаги\n1. **Update PRD**: Change Q2 answer from JWT-claims to custom header-based auth\n2. **Add Dependencies**: spring-boot-starter-security, spring-boot-starter-websocket (if WebSocket chosen)\n3. **Create Database Migration**: audit_log table with Liquibase\n4. **Implement RBAC Filter**: Spring WebFlux filter for POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints\n5. **Extend Profile Store**: Add real-time role sync (SSE or WebSocket)\n6. **Create Audit Service**: Log GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED operations\n\n## Дополнительные заметки\n\n### Current Database Schema (PostgreSQL)\n- **Existing tables**: note_entry, note_vector_store, repo_rag_*\n- **Pattern**: UUID primary keys, JSONB for metadata, created_at/updated_at timestamps\n- **User identification**: user_namespace + user_reference (see NoteEntity.java:40-44)\n\n### Frontend Dependencies\n- **State**: Zustand (not Redux)\n- **HTTP**: Native fetch\n- **Validation**: Zod\n- **Real-time**: EventSource (SSE) for flows\n\n### Backend Dependencies (build.gradle)\n- **Web**: spring-boot-starter-webflux\n- **Data**: spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, postgresql\n- **No security**: spring-boot-starter-security missing\n- **No WebSocket**: spring-boot-starter-websocket missing\n\n### Profile API Contract\n- **Headers**: X-Profile-Key (format: `namespace:reference`), X-Profile-Auth (dev token)\n- **Role format**: Array of strings (`roles: [\"admin\", \"user\"]`)\n- **Admin check**: Presence of `\"admin\"` in roles array\n\n## Открытые вопросы\n1. **Q1**: Should we add Spring Security or implement custom WebFlux filters for RBAC?\n2. **Q2**: Should we use existing SSE or implement WebSocket for role sync?\n3. **Q3**: How should backend fetch profile roles? Cache or call profile service on each request?\n4. **Q4**: What is the source of truth for roles? Profile service or local RBAC tables?\n"}}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":70685,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":70685,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_RfJjc02EpvEzKQgTt0ipq88l","session_id":"9c606146-0f99-4e7f-bc70-a7a06f289760","uuid":"47e17386-34fe-447d-9557-9948c5d57c97"}
