{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_RfJjc02EpvEzKQgTt0ipq88l","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Research Complete\n\nI have completed the comprehensive research for ticket TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement. Here is the summary:\n\n### Status: reviewed\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**1. Current Auth State (No JWT/Security)**\n- No Spring Security in classpath (`build.gradle` lacks `spring-boot-starter-security`)\n- No JWT infrastructure found\n- Custom header-based authentication using `X-Profile-Key`, `X-Profile-Channel`, `X-Profile-Auth`\n- Profile identity format: `{namespace}:{reference}`\n\n**2. Frontend State Management (Zustand, not Redux)**\n- Uses Zustand with persistence (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n- Profile document includes `roles: string[]` array\n- Admin check pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n\n**3. Existing Route Guards**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45` - Conditional Admin nav link based on role\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36` - Admin role check before showing admin panel\n\n**4. Real-time Infrastructure (SSE exists, no WebSocket)**\n- SSE (Server-Sent Events) already implemented for flow sessions and MCP chat\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` has `subscribeToFlowEvents()`\n- No WebSocket infrastructure found\n\n**5. Database Schema**\n- PostgreSQL with Liquibase migrations\n- Existing tables: `note_entry`, `note_vector_store`, `repo_rag_*`\n- No `audit_log` table exists\n- Pattern: UUID PK, JSONB metadata, created_at/updated_at timestamps\n\n**6. No Existing RBAC/Security**\n- No `@PreAuthorize`, `@Secured`, or security annotations\n- No `SecurityConfig` class\n- No 403/401 handling infrastructure\n\n### Research Report Location\n`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n### Key Gaps Identified\n1. PRD assumes JWT-claims auth, but codebase uses custom header auth\n2. PRD mentions Redux, but actual code uses Zustand\n3. PRD requires WebSocket, but SSE exists and could be reused\n4. No Spring Security dependency\n5. No audit_log table\n\n### Next Stage\n/feature-dev-aidd:plan-new TST-001"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a27fedf177f6a1f65 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75226\ntool_uses: 59\nduration_ms: 300653</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c606146-0f99-4e7f-bc70-a7a06f289760","uuid":"9464627c-9a5f-4b53-bd18-56bb55658fd9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Research the codebase for ticket TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement.\n\n## Project Structure\nThis is a Java Spring MCP backend + React TypeScript frontend:\n- Backend: `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/` - Java Spring MCP server\n- Frontend: `frontend/src/` - React + TypeScript frontend\n\n## Research Goals\nPer the PRD (aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md), research:\n1. Find existing JWT/auth configuration in the Java backend\n2. Find existing role/permission checks anywhere in the codebase\n3. Find frontend auth flow (Redux/Context for auth state)\n4. Find existing route guards on frontend\n5. Check for any WebSocket infrastructure\n6. Find database models/entities for users, roles, permissions\n7. Find any existing audit logging infrastructure\n\n## Key Files to Check\n- Backend config files (look for SecurityConfig, JWT, auth)\n- Backend properties files\n- Frontend store files (profileStore.ts, etc.)\n- Frontend pages that might have Admin roles (AdminRoles.tsx)\n\n## Output\nCreate a comprehensive research report at `docs/research/TST-001.md` with:\n- Summary of current auth/RBAC state\n- Integration points for new RBAC middleware\n- Frontend state management analysis\n- Database schema findings\n- WebSocket infrastructure status\n- Recommendations for implementation\n\nUse RLM evidence gathering pattern: document file paths, line numbers, and exact code snippets found.","agentId":"a27fedf177f6a1f65","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Research Complete\n\nI have completed the comprehensive research for ticket TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement. Here is the summary:\n\n### Status: reviewed\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**1. Current Auth State (No JWT/Security)**\n- No Spring Security in classpath (`build.gradle` lacks `spring-boot-starter-security`)\n- No JWT infrastructure found\n- Custom header-based authentication using `X-Profile-Key`, `X-Profile-Channel`, `X-Profile-Auth`\n- Profile identity format: `{namespace}:{reference}`\n\n**2. Frontend State Management (Zustand, not Redux)**\n- Uses Zustand with persistence (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n- Profile document includes `roles: string[]` array\n- Admin check pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n\n**3. Existing Route Guards**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45` - Conditional Admin nav link based on role\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36` - Admin role check before showing admin panel\n\n**4. Real-time Infrastructure (SSE exists, no WebSocket)**\n- SSE (Server-Sent Events) already implemented for flow sessions and MCP chat\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` has `subscribeToFlowEvents()`\n- No WebSocket infrastructure found\n\n**5. Database Schema**\n- PostgreSQL with Liquibase migrations\n- Existing tables: `note_entry`, `note_vector_store`, `repo_rag_*`\n- No `audit_log` table exists\n- Pattern: UUID PK, JSONB metadata, created_at/updated_at timestamps\n\n**6. No Existing RBAC/Security**\n- No `@PreAuthorize`, `@Secured`, or security annotations\n- No `SecurityConfig` class\n- No 403/401 handling infrastructure\n\n### Research Report Location\n`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n\n### Key Gaps Identified\n1. PRD assumes JWT-claims auth, but codebase uses custom header auth\n2. PRD mentions Redux, but actual code uses Zustand\n3. PRD requires WebSocket, but SSE exists and could be reused\n4. No Spring Security dependency\n5. No audit_log table\n\n### Next Stage\n/feature-dev-aidd:plan-new TST-001"}],"totalDurationMs":300653,"totalTokens":75226,"totalToolUseCount":59,"usage":{"input_tokens":3980,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":70656,"output_tokens":590,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
